Such cryptocurrencies are an environmental disaster. Worse, they can be replicated without bound, further amplifying the environmental damage. As at March 29, CoinMarketCap listed 4,490 cryptocurrencies, starting with Bitcoin (with a $1.08 trillion market cap) and followed by Ethereum ($204 billion). 

Bitcoin is an excessively risky and environmentally undesirable investment. It is not a sensible solution to any emerging-market problem and cannot be a store of value or reliable medium of exchange. The sooner such DLT-based cryptocurrencies are relegated to a footnote in economic history, the better. The law change drive is facing a timeline nightmare even as Parliament goes on a one-month recess. The government’s appetite for debt shot up by 69 per cent between March 2020 and March 2021. Senator is touring counties, holding strategy meetings with advisers and regional leaders.